<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The Plate of Origin finale aired on Seven on Tuesday and absolutely tanked.  </p>

<p>As Mumbrella reports, the final episode was the lowest rating episode of the entire season, no doubt a major blow for the network. </p>

<p>The publication reports that for the three-hour double episode finale, 349,000 metro viewers tuned in for the first part, while just 335,000 watched the second. </p>

<p>Sorry boys! Seven's Plate of Origin finale on Tuesday suffered the worst ratings of the entire SEASON - as just 335,000 tuned in to watch Team Greece win $100,000. Pictured are judges (from left to right) Matt Preston, Manu Feildel and Gary Mehigan </p>

<p>The Block meanwhile won the night, with 807,000 viewers. </p>

<p>It comes after Plate of Origin drew in 667,000 for the premiere.  </p>

<p>On Tuesday night's three-hour grand final episode of Plate Of Origin, Team Greece emerged victorious.</p>

<p>Winners: On Tuesday night's three-hour grand final episode of Plate Of Origin, Team Greece emerged victorious. Cousins Dezi, 41, and Penny, 33, (pictured) were crowned Plate of Origin champions winning $100,000</p>

<p>Cousins Dezi, 41, and Penny, 33, were crowned Plate of Origin champions winning $100,000.</p>

<p>They received a total judges' score of 76/90 after a three-course meal showdown with Team Vietnam's Thanh, 31, and Duncan, 30.</p>

<p>Dezi said of their win: 'We have represented the Australian Greek community and now we've just won Plate of Origin!'</p>

<p>Shocked: Dezi said of their win: 'We have represented the Australian Greek community and now we've just won Plate of Origin!'</p>

<p>'It is mind-blowing. I'm so grateful, this is beyond anything I could have ever dreamed of.'</p>

<p>When asked by judge Matt Preston if Greek cuisine was the best in the world, Penny added: 'Of course it is!' </p>

<p>Team Greece secured an early lead with their entrée featuring perfectly cooked prawns, while Team Vietnam's Rice Paper Rolls unravelled with undercooked Morton Bay Bug. </p>

<p>What a slide: It comes after Plate of Origin drew in 667,000 viewers for the premiere</p>
